IRI.description: The Internationalized Resource Identifier (IRI) is and internet protocol standard that builds on the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) protocol, extending the set of permitted characters to include Unicode/ISO 10646.
IRI.name: IRI

abstractionLevel.description: The abstraction level indicates the extend of simplification of physical, spatial, or temporal details or attributes in the study of objects or systems.
abstractionLevel.name: Abstraction level
